The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Day V highlights
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Day V highlights
                      
	Gautam Gambhir (276 runs) bettered his own record of most runs scored in a match. His previous best was 242 vs Australia in Delhi, 2008-09.         
	Gambhir has now scored the most runs in a match in Mohali. The previous best was 252 (174 .. amp; 78) by Jimmy Adams of the West Indies in 1994-95.         
	Gambhir also bettered the record of Vinoo Mankad for most runs in a Test against England. Mankad had scored 256 runs at Lords in 1952.         
	Gambhir became the third Indian after Vinoo Mankad and Sachin Tendulkar (251 runs  177 amp; 74  Trent Bridge,1996) to score more than 250 runs in a Test against England. Gambhir is the first Indian to do so on home soil.         
	Gambhir (824 in 2008-09) is currently in fourth position in the list of most runs scored in an Indian cricket season. The top three are Virender Sehwag (1105 in 2004-05); Sunil Gavaskar (1027 in 1979-80) and Dilip Vengsarkar (966 in 1986-87).         
	The partnership of 153 for the fifth wicket between Gambhir and Yuvraj Singh is now the best for the fifth wicket in Mohali.         
	Gambhir became the fourth Indian to miss out on a century in each innings . The others being CG Borde (109 amp; 96 vs WI, Delhi 1958-59); M Amarnath (90 amp; 100 vs Aus, Perth 1977-78); S Ganguly (239 amp; 91 vs Pak, Bangalore 2007-08)                                                                                                                          
